<p>Most Islamic scholars of interpretation mentioned that seeing rain in a dream is one of the praiseworthy signs of abundant sustenance, multiple blessings, and goodness in one's life. Praying for rain also proves one's closeness to God Almighty and their steadfastness. The desire to be content with piety and righteous deeds. Generally, the dream indicates the good state of one's circumstances and the presence of a stable atmosphere between the dreamer and their family members, which puts them in a good psychological state.</p>
<p><span></span></p>
<p>Seeing a plea is one of the dreams that foretells good news for the dreamer, depending on their marital status, whether they are single or married. It indicates that they will achieve what they want in life from their goals and aspirations. And pleading for marriage and mentioning the name of the desired person are promising signs of marrying this very person in real life, God willing.</p>
<h2><strong>Dream Interpretation of Praying for Marriage to a Specific Person Under the Rain by <a href="https://gptafser.com/post/تفسير-حلم-ابن-سيرين-في-المنام?page=1665" > Ibn Sirin </a></strong></h2>
<p><a href="https://gptafser.com/post/تفسير-حلم-ابن-سيرين-في-المنام?page=1665" > Ibn Sirin </a> explained many good signs of seeing praying in the rain in a dream. If the prayer is for marriage to a specific person, then this indicates the good fortune of the seer and their success in choosing a life partner, thus leading to a passionate and loving family life filled with love and harmony because there is harmony and great appreciation between them. The dream is also considered a good omen that they are about to achieve the hopes and aspirations they have been striving for for a long time and thought were difficult to achieve.</p><div class="angwp_84394 _ning_cont _ning_hidden _ning_outer _align_center responsive" data-aid="0" data-bid="84394" data-size="custom" style="max-width:100%; width:100%;height:inherit;"><div class="_ning_label _left" style=""></div><div class="_ning_inner" style=""><script type="text/javascript">
